title: Smile best who smile last
description: Model combining Facenet and VGG in KerasThis is my single best scoring model (0.893 public leaderboard, 0.900 private leaderboard) I used this model in combination with other 36 models to get my final submission. From the 37 models that I used, 7 are public kernels (reference below) https://www.kaggle.com/shivamsarawagi/wildimagedetection-0-875 https://www.kaggle.com/hsinwenchang/vggface-baseline-197x197 https://www.kaggle.com/arjunrao2000/kinship-detection-with-vgg16 https://www.kaggle.com/leonbora/kinship-recognition-transfer-learning-vggface https://www.kaggle.com/janpreets/just-another-feature-extractor-0-824-lb https://www.kaggle.com/tenffe/vggface-cv-focal-loss https://www.kaggle.com/vaishvik25/smile I used pretrained Facenet model from this repo https://github.com/nyoki-mtl/keras-facenet).
